# Authorization

- Layer 1 (authentication) is the Apollo plugin gate in `src/Graphql/GraphqlServer.ts`: every operation requires an authenticated principal before execution starts. Never add per-operation auth by weakening the gate; public queries go in the `publicQueryRootFields` allowlist.
- Layer 2 (authorization) lives in services, never resolvers: mutating service methods take `actingUserId` on their request object and check membership/roles up front (exemplar: `ProjectService.updateProject` → `requireProjectRole`).
- Resolvers only translate `context.principal` into `actingUserId`, throwing `UNAUTHENTICATED` when there is no application user.
- `UNAUTHENTICATED` = unknown caller; `PERMISSION_DENIED` = known caller, insufficient role. Never swap them.
- New restricted domains need blackbox tests for: anonymous, non-member, insufficient role, allowed role (see `test/Project/AuthorizationTest.ts`).
- Full guide: `docs/authorization.md`.
